    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently a *truthy* (i.e. anything other than `nil` or `false` in Lua) return value in the callback for `nvim_create_autocmd` deletes the autocmd after execution.\n\nThis is useful, but it can lead to unwanted behavior and [subtle problems](https://github.com/Olical/nfnl/commit/ac0177c5549df7abba7a19554c18a7765386c894) in language like Fennel, where expression values are automatically returned and is truthy in many situations.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n@justinmk has proposed that it's possible to limit the value triggering deletion to `true` instead of anything truthy. This is going to be a breaking change, and feedback is wanted from people who are depending on this behavior.\n\nPossibly related: #27484 (well that's quite a back-and-forth if this is changed again...)",
